  <section xml:id="wb.ProjectExplorerCopyRenameDeleteActions">
    <title>Copy, Rename and Delete Actions</title>
    <para>Copy, rename and delete actions are available on <emphasis role="italic">Links </emphasis> mode, for packages
      (in of Project View) and for files and directories as well (in Repository View).</para>
    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para> A : Copy</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para> B : Rename</para>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para> C : Delete</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <figure>
      <title>Project View - Package actions</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/Workbench/Authoring/ProjectExplorer/ProjectExplorer-Project-Links-Copy-Rename-Delete.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <figure>
      <title>Repository View - Files and directories actions</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/Workbench/Authoring/ProjectExplorer/ProjectExplorer-Repository-Copy-Rename-Delete.png"/>
        </imageobject>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    
    <warning>
      <para>Workbench roadmap includes a refactoring and an impact analyses tools, but currenctly doesn't have it. Until
        both tools are provided make sure that your changes (copy/rename/delete) on packages, files or directories
        doesn't have a major impact on your project.</para>
      <para>In cases that your change had an unexcepcted impact, Workbench allows you to restore your repository using
        the <link linkend="wb.VFSRepositoryEditor">Repository editor</link>.</para>
    </warning>
    
